{{unreferenced|date=May 2011}} {{Infobox person | honorific_prefix = | name = Baron do Rio da Prata | honorific_suffix = | image = Pinto Guedes.png | alt = | caption = | birth_name = Rodrigo Pinto Guedes | birth_date = {{Birth date|df=yes|1762|07|27}} | birth_place = Gradiz, [[Portugal]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|df=yes|1845|06|13|1762|07|27}} | death_place = [[Paris]], [[France]] | nationality = | other_names = | known_for = Commander of all the [[Empire of Brazil]] naval operations during the Cisplatine War | occupation, succeeding [[Rodrigues Lobo]]= }} '''Rodrigo Pinto Guedes, 1st Baron do Rio da Prata''' (July 27, 1762 in [[Gradiz]], [[Portugal]] &ndash; June 13, 1845 in [[Paris]]) was a naval officer who served in the admiralties of the [[Kingdom of Portugal]], its successor the [[United Kingdom of Portugal, Brazil and the Algarves]], and finally the [[Empire of Brazil]], for which he acted as commander of all naval operations during the [[Cisplatine War]].
==Biography== Guedes was born on July 27, 1762 in [[Aguiar da Beira]], [[Gradiz]], [[Portugal]] to Rodrigo Pinto Guedes and Maria da Silveira Pereira. His parents intended him to take on a religious life, and sent him to a monastery; however, he ran away and decided to embark on a maritime career. In September 1781, he was named a Cadet of the Portuguese Navy, and thus began what would prove to be a successful career.
He married Constanza Smissaert Pinto Caldas, daughter of Jos√© Pereira Caldas and Constanza Smissaert.
